params.account: Address to check badge balance (= value of attestation)

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

claimWithSismoConnect(bytes,address,uint.details: Mints a ZK Badge based on a Sismo Connect response Each appId is mapped to a ZK Badge configuration. the vaultId provided in the response must not have minted a ZK Badge for this appId yet. The vaultId is used to prevent double spending of a ZK Badge for a specific appId.

params.responseBytes: Response from Sismo Connect in a bytes format
params.to: Address of the receiver of the ZK Badge
params.tokenId: TokenId of the ZK Badge to mint

params.legacyUri: Legacy uri for the metadata of badges
params.owner: Owner of the contract, super admin, can setup roles and update the attestation registry

getAttributeValueForBadge(uint256,uint8).details: Getter of the value of a specific badge attribute

getAttributesNamesAndValuesForBadge(uint.details: Getter of all badge attributes and their values for a specific badge

getBadgeExtraData(address,uint256).details: Getter of the badge extra data (it can store nullifier and burnCount)

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getZKBadgeConfig(uint256).details: Returns the ZK Badge configuration based on its appId

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

initialize(string,address).details: Initializes the contract, to be called by the proxy delegating calls to this implementation

params.owner: Owner of the contract, super admin, can setup roles and update the attestation registry

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Reverts, this is a non transferable ERC115 contract

isVaultIdUsedForTokenId(uint256,uint256).details: Returns if weither or not a vaultId has minted a specific ZK Badge

params.vaultId: anonymous identifier of a user's vault for a specific app

registerZKBadgeConfig(bytes16,bool,strin.details: Registers a ZK Badge configuration The function can only be called by the super admin. The config can be registered one time only. It is then possible to update the config if you are the owner for this config. This config allows to setup: - the uri of the ZK Badge - the Sismo Connect configuration - the auths and claims required to mint the ZK Badge - the owner of the ZK Badge configuration - the tokenId of the ZK Badge

params.appId: id of the Sismo Connect App from which the proofs are required
params.authRequests: list of dataSource ownerships required to mint the ZK Badge
params.claimRequests: list of group memberships required to mint the ZK Badge
params.isImpersonationMode: if True, the ZK Badge can be minted thanks to impersonated proofs
params.owner: owner of the ZK Badge configuration
params.tokenURI: uri of the ZK Badge metadata

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Reverts, this is a non transferable ERC115 contract

setAttestationsRegistry(address).details: Set the attestations registry address. Can only be called by owner (default admin)

setLegacyUri(string).details: Set the URI for legacy ZK Badges. Can only be called by owner (default admin)

setUri(string).details: Set the URI for Sismo Connect ZK Badges. Can only be called by owner (default admin)

triggerTransferEvent(address,address,add.details: Emits a TransferSingle event, so subgraphs and other off-chain apps relying on events can see badge minting/burning can only be called by address having the EVENT_TRIGGERER_ROLE (attestations registry address)

params.from: address(0) if minting, address of the badge holder if burning
params.id: badgeId for which to trigger the event
params.to: address of the badge holder is minting, address(0) if burning

updateZKBadgeConfig(bytes16,bool,string,.details: Updates a ZK Badge configuration The function can only be called by the owner of the ZK Badge configuration. This config allows to setup:

params.appId: id of the Sismo Connect App from which the proofs are required
params.authRequests: list of dataSource ownerships required to mint the ZK Badge
params.claimRequests: list of group memberships required to mint the ZK Badge
params.isImpersonationMode: if True, the ZK Badge can be minted thanks to impersonated proofs
params.owner: owner of the ZK Badge configuration
params.tokenURI: uri of the ZK Badge metadata

uri(uint256).details: Returns the uri of a ZK Badge based on its tokenId

balanceOf(address,uint256).notice: For all legacy tokenIds, the balance of a user is equal to the value of the underlying attestation (attestationCollectionId == badgeId) For ZK Badges V2 tokenIds, the balance is equal to the amount of token owned by a vaultId
